author: app.com
title: Rutgers star Leonte Carroo among 3 questionable vs. Wisconsin
text:
MORE PISCATAWAY - It's another "Will he or won't he?" week for Leonte Carroo.
Rutgers star wide receiver is questionable on the team's official injury report ahead of Saturday's game at Wisconsin.
Carroo carried the same designation last week and did not practice Tuesday or Wednesday before participating in Thursday's walk-through. There is no media availability after Friday practices.
"I think it will be a very similar situation to last week where we are not going to know until the end of the week what we think the situation will be," coach Kyle Flood said.
Carroo made three catches for 55 yards in the first half against Ohio State but did not play in the second half because he was "physically unable to perform," according to Flood.
The injury dates back to a third-quarter touchdown catch Oct. 17 at Indiana, when it appeared Carroo hurt his ankle after squeezing between two defenders to make the grab.
